$ mkdir --help
$ mkdir FOLDER_NAME
$ mkdir FOLDER_NAME{NO..NO}
EG: mkdir Dir{1..5}                                                 (will create 5 directories using Noâ€™s)  
$ mkdir -v FOLDER_NAME
$ mkdir -p FOLDER_NAME/FOLDER_NAME/FOLDER_NAME                      (create parent directories, check if directories exist OR not exist in location path)    
$ mkdir -pv FOLDER_NAME/FOLDER_NAME
$ mkdir -p -v FOLDER_NAME/FOLDER_NAME
$ mkdir -m a=rwx FOLDER_NAME                                        (permission for the created directories)
